CATAGORY1.name: Floor Tiles
CATAGORY1.description: Floor tiles are best to make interior and exterior space stylish and desirable. Whether its about modern designs or any typical classy look and feels, our floor tiles has a unique finishes, colors, style and designs compatible for interior as well as exterior spaces.

CATAGORY1.name: Showpiece
CATAGORY1.description: With a futuristic look, owing to graphical symmetry and its clever color scheme, The Showpiece sticks true to its name and celebrates the feminine silhouette and the beauty of fashion. This is a must have for the fashion lover! This is designed by Piet Paris, a successful fashion illustrator who uses the woman as a central point of attention and sketches a graphic interplay of lines that reflect his love of fashion.

CATAGORY1.name: Double Charge
CATAGORY1.description: Double charge vitrified tiles are fed through a press that prints the pattern with a double layer of pigment, 3 to 4 mm thicker than other types of tile. This process does not permit complex patterns but results in a long-wearing tile surface, suitable for heavy traffic commercial projects.

CATAGORY1.name: Wooden & Matt
CATAGORY1.description: Get creative with different sizes of wood tiles and distinctive patterns. And don't limit yourself to the floor; adding this wood tile to walls will create a peaceful nature-inspired appearance. Wood look tiles are one of the key trends for indoor and outdoor floor, capturing the beauty of natural timber and combining it with the durability of porcelain tiles.

CATAGORY1.name: Kitchen
CATAGORY1.description: Of all the rooms in the house, the kitchen is the zone where tiles flourish. Ceramic tiles can handle the heat of hot pots and pans, while obviously linoleum can not.

CATAGORY1.name: Granite
CATAGORY1.description: Graniteâ€™s natural beauty is one of the main reasons that people choose it as a flooring material. One of the greatest assets that comes with a granite floor is its durability. granite is very resistant to moisture and can be used with little worry in kitchens or bathrooms. It is also resistant to stains, like those from acidic foods, which is what makes it so ideal as a material for countertops.
